<!-- ============ PAGE 5: FAQ ============ -->
<section class="faq" id="faq">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <h1 class="section-headline">Trust Center & FAQ</h1>
    <div class="faq-search">
      <input type="text" placeholder="Search security, pricing, integrations..." id="faq-search-input">
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-cat-title">Security & Privacy</h3>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">How does the "20% Public Data" work?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Scotty automatically aggregates official, publicly available budget documents, transparency reports, and legislative records for your agency to give you an immediate "Aha!" moment of analysis—at no cost, with no login required beyond legislative verification.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is my internal data safe once I get licensed and integrate?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Absolutely. We use the "Performa Shield" architecture. Your internal data is ingested into a private AI instance that only your authorized staff can access. It is never mixed with public data, never shared across agencies, and never used to train external AI models.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-cat-title">How the AI Copilot Works</h3>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Can Scotty integrate with our current BIDS or DOTS platform?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Scotty is designed by the same team that built the BIDS and DOTS systems. Integration is seamless via secure API or batch upload—no middleware, no expensive IT project required. Most agencies are live within a single sprint cycle.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Does Scotty replace our existing financial software?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No—Scotty is an intelligence layer, not a replacement. It sits on top of your existing systems and transforms raw financial data into actionable insights. Think of it as giving your existing tools an AI brain.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-cat-title">Data Integration (The 80/20 Rule)</h3>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">What exactly is the "80/20 data model"?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>With the free tier, Scotty gives you instant access to all publicly available budget records — legislative filings, transparency reports, public BIDS data. This represents roughly 20% of your agency's full financial picture. To unlock the rest, simply get licensed. We handle the full integration of your internal systems — line items, project ledgers, grant tracking — so you get 100% of the intelligence, with none of the IT headache.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-category">
        <h3 class="faq-cat-title">Pricing & Procurement</h3>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is Scotty available on government procurement vehicles?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Scotty is available through GSA Schedule and various state cooperative purchasing agreements. The Performa Group's 20-year relationship with government procurement offices means we understand the process and can support your agency's specific contracting requirements.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">Is there a free tier for legislative staff?<span class="faq-toggle">+</span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. The "Verified Public Access" tier is permanently free for verified legislative staff. It provides access to the 20% public data insights for your district, with basic trend analysis and report generation—no credit card, no time limit.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="post-faq-ctas">
      <h3>Still Have Questions?</h3>
      <div class="post-faq-buttons">
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline">Contact Sales</a>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-red">Request Technical SLA</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

